    type='think',
    think='The `SwipeCardStack` test fails because `Image.network` throws except
ions in widget tests when trying to load network images. Even though there\'s an
`errorBuilder`, the initial load attempt throws an exception that the test frame
work catches.\n\nIn Flutter widget tests, `Image.network` will fail because ther
e\'s no network. The `errorBuilder` should handle it, but the test framework mig
ht still report uncaught exceptions.\n\nA common solution is to wrap the widget 
in a `MaterialApp` with a custom `imageCache` or use `HttpOverrides` to mock net
work images. Or simpler: use empty avatar URLs so the placeholder is shown inste
ad of Image.network.\n\nIn the golden test for `SwipeCardStack`, I used real net
work URLs (`https://i.pravatar.cc/300?img=5`). If I change them to empty strings
, the `_buildPlaceholder()` will be used instead.\n\nLet me update the golden te
st to use empty avatar URLs. This is a reasonable approach for golden tests sinc
e we want to test the widget structure, not the actual image loading.\n\nActuall
y, looking at the test output again, the error says "Multiple exceptions (31) we
re detected". This suggests a lot of Image.network failures. Let me update the g
olden test to use empty URLs.',
    encrypted=None
)
